@startuml Network Architecture - Maritime System

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #F5F5F5

title Network Architecture & Communication Boundaries

' Define network zones
rectangle "Internet Zone\n(Public Access)" as internet_zone #FFEBEE {
    rectangle "Authentication Frontend" as auth_ui #E8EAF6
    rectangle "Core Frontend" as core_ui #E8EAF6
}

rectangle "DMZ Zone\n(Gateway Layer)" as dmz_zone #E8F5E8 {
    rectangle "Gateway Service\n(Port 8080)" as gateway #C8E6C9
    database "Security DB\n(Port 5433)" as sec_db #E1BEE7
    database "Security Redis\n(Port 6380)" as sec_redis #FFE0B2
}

rectangle "Internal Zone\n(Backend Services)" as internal_zone #FFF3E0 {
    rectangle "Core Backend\n(Port 8000)" as backend #FFCC80
    database "Core Redis\n(Port 6379)" as core_redis #FFECB3
}

rectangle "Cloud Zone\n(External Services)" as cloud_zone #E3F2FD {
    database "Cloud PostgreSQL\n(Render.com)" as cloud_db #BBDEFB
}

' Network connections
auth_ui --> gateway : "HTTPS\nPort 8080"
core_ui --> gateway : "HTTPS\nPort 8080"

gateway --> sec_db : "Internal\nPort 5433"
gateway --> sec_redis : "Internal\nPort 6380"
gateway --> backend : "Internal\nPort 8000"

backend --> core_redis : "Internal\nPort 6379"
backend --> cloud_db : "Encrypted\nInternet"

' Network boundaries
note bottom of internet_zone
  **PUBLIC NETWORK**
  - Direct internet access
  - Browser-based clients
  - HTTPS/TLS encryption
end note

note bottom of dmz_zone
  **DMZ / GATEWAY NETWORK**
  - Controlled access point
  - Authentication & authorization
  - Request validation
  - Docker bridge network
end note

note bottom of internal_zone
  **INTERNAL NETWORK**
  - Backend services only
  - Business logic layer
  - Isolated from direct internet
  - Docker bridge network
end note

note bottom of cloud_zone
  **CLOUD NETWORK**
  - Managed service provider
  - External connectivity
  - Encrypted connections only
  - High availability
end note

' Data flow indicators
note on link between gateway and backend
  **Service-to-Service**
  - Internal HTTP
  - Service mesh
  - Health checks
end note

note on link between backend and cloud_db
  **Cloud Integration**
  - TLS encryption
  - Connection pooling
  - Retry logic
end note

' Security boundaries
rectangle "Security Boundary" as sec_boundary #FFCDD2
sec_boundary --> internet_zone
sec_boundary --> dmz_zone

note right of sec_boundary
  **Security Layers**
  1. Internet firewall
  2. Gateway authentication
  3. Internal network isolation
  4. Cloud encryption
end note

@enduml
